         <div type="translation">
            <p>The council and the people honoured Mithradates son of Athenagoras, a fine and good man, and adorned with all virtue.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This text was one of a group cut on the family tomb whose elements were incorporated into the walls at the south east gate of the city: <ref type="inscription" n="1001" target="120410.xml"/> (= MAMA 462), <ref type="inscription" n="1010" target="130302.xml"/> (=474, 475, 476) and <ref type="inscription" n="369" target="120409.xml"/> (Walls 151) The group is published and discussed by <bibl n="jmr1991a">Reynolds 1999</bibl>.</p>
            <p>.</p>
         </div>
